metadata.description: Clean FitCoachConnect database backup - 5 class types, 25 exercises

classTypes.name: HIIT
classTypes.description: A time-efficient workout method alternating between short bursts of intense exercise and brief recovery periods to maximize calorie burn and improve cardiovascular fitness.

classTypes.name: Pilates
classTypes.description: A low-impact exercise method focusing on core strength, flexibility, and body awareness through controlled, precise movements and proper breathing techniques.

classTypes.name: Spinning/Indoor Cycling
classTypes.description: An intense cardiovascular workout performed on stationary bikes, featuring music-driven sessions with varied resistance and speed to simulate outdoor cycling conditions.

classTypes.name: Yoga
classTypes.description: A mind-body practice combining physical postures, breathing techniques, and meditation to improve flexibility, strength, balance, and mental well-being.

classTypes.name: Zumba
classTypes.description: A high-energy dance fitness program that combines Latin and international music with dance moves, creating a fun, party-like atmosphere while providing an effective cardio workout.

exercises.name: Roll Up
exercises.description: Slowly rolling up from lying to seated position using core control
exercises.modifications: Bend knees, use hands for assistance, partial roll up
exercises.safety_notes: Move slowly and controlled, don't force the movement

exercises.name: Rolling Like a Ball
exercises.description: Balancing on tailbone and rolling backward and forward
exercises.modifications: Hold behind thighs, smaller rolling motion, rock gently
exercises.safety_notes: Keep chin to chest, control the roll, avoid rolling on neck

exercises.name: Single Leg Circles
exercises.description: Lying down, drawing circles in the air with one extended leg
exercises.modifications: Smaller circles, bend supporting leg, hold thigh for support
exercises.safety_notes: Keep hips stable, control the movement, don't let back arch

exercises.name: Single Leg Stretch
exercises.description: Alternating knee-to-chest pulls while extending the opposite leg
exercises.modifications: Keep head down, higher leg extension, slower pace
exercises.safety_notes: Keep lower back pressed into mat, switch legs smoothly

exercises.name: The Hundred
exercises.description: Lying on back, pumping arms while holding legs in tabletop position
exercises.modifications: Keep head down, bend knees, reduce arm pumping
exercises.safety_notes: Keep lower back pressed into mat, breathe rhythmically

exercises.name: Child's Pose
exercises.description: A resting pose kneeling with arms extended forward and forehead on the ground
exercises.modifications: Place pillow under forehead, widen knees for more comfort
exercises.safety_notes: Avoid if you have knee injuries, can sit on heels if more comfortable

exercises.name: Downward Facing Dog
exercises.description: An inverted V-shape pose with hands and feet on the ground, stretching the entire body
exercises.modifications: Place forearms on ground for easier variation, use blocks under hands for support
exercises.safety_notes: Keep slight bend in knees if hamstrings are tight, avoid if you have wrist injuries

exercises.name: Tree Pose
exercises.description: A standing balance pose with one foot placed on the opposite leg's thigh or calf
exercises.modifications: Hold wall for support, place foot on ankle instead of calf/thigh
exercises.safety_notes: Never place foot on side of knee, use wall or chair for balance if needed

exercises.name: Warrior I
exercises.description: A standing lunge pose with arms raised overhead, building strength and stability
exercises.modifications: Use blocks under hands, shorten stance for easier balance
exercises.safety_notes: Keep front knee aligned over ankle, avoid if you have hip injuries

exercises.name: Warrior II
exercises.description: A wide-legged stance with arms extended parallel to the ground, opening the hips
exercises.modifications: Place forearm on front thigh for support, use wall for balance
exercises.safety_notes: Keep front knee tracking over ankle, don't let knee cave inward

exercises.name: Basic Salsa Step
exercises.description: A rhythmic step-together-step pattern moving side to side with hip action
exercises.modifications: Reduce hip movement, step in place instead of side to side
exercises.safety_notes: Wear proper dance shoes, keep movements controlled

exercises.name: Cha-Cha-Cha
exercises.description: A quick triple-step pattern with a rock step, creating a lively rhythm
exercises.modifications: Slow down the tempo, simplify footwork
exercises.safety_notes: Start slowly to learn the pattern, keep movements light and quick

exercises.name: Cumbia Step
exercises.description: A side-to-side stepping pattern with a slight rocking motion
exercises.modifications: Smaller steps, less hip movement
exercises.safety_notes: Keep weight centered, avoid overextending steps

exercises.name: Merengue March
exercises.description: A simple marching step in place with alternating knee lifts and arm swings
exercises.modifications: Lower knee lifts, reduce arm movement
exercises.safety_notes: Land softly on balls of feet, maintain good posture

exercises.name: Reggaeton Bounce
exercises.description: A bouncing movement with bent knees and rhythmic up-and-down motion
exercises.modifications: Reduce bounce height, hold onto something for balance
exercises.safety_notes: Keep knees soft, land on balls of feet to reduce impact

exercises.name: Burpees
exercises.description: A full-body movement combining a squat, plank, push-up, and jump
exercises.modifications: Step back instead of jumping, remove push-up, no jump at the end
exercises.safety_notes: Land softly, maintain good form throughout, modify as needed

exercises.name: High Knees
exercises.description: Running in place while lifting knees as high as possible
exercises.modifications: Lower knee height, marching in place instead of running
exercises.safety_notes: Land on balls of feet, maintain good posture, pump arms naturally

exercises.name: Jump Squats
exercises.description: Squatting down and explosively jumping up, landing softly
exercises.modifications: Regular squats without jumping, smaller jump height
exercises.safety_notes: Land softly on balls of feet, keep knees aligned, proper squat form

exercises.name: Mountain Climbers
exercises.description: A plank position with alternating knee drives toward the chest
exercises.modifications: Slow down the pace, place hands on elevated surface
exercises.safety_notes: Maintain plank position, keep hips level, engage core

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: A classic upper body exercise lowering and pressing the body up from the ground
exercises.modifications: Knee push-ups, wall push-ups, incline push-ups
exercises.safety_notes: Keep body in straight line, lower slowly, full range of motion

exercises.name: Jumps (Seated to Standing)
exercises.description: Alternating between seated and standing positions in rhythm
exercises.modifications: Longer intervals between position changes, lower resistance
exercises.safety_notes: Smooth transitions, engage core, maintain bike control

exercises.name: Seated Climb
exercises.description: Seated pedaling with increased resistance to build leg strength
exercises.modifications: Moderate resistance increase, maintain comfortable cadence
exercises.safety_notes: Keep upper body relaxed, don't grip handlebars too tightly

exercises.name: Seated Flat Road
exercises.description: Basic seated pedaling position with moderate resistance for endurance building
exercises.modifications: Lower resistance, slower cadence
exercises.safety_notes: Proper bike fit essential, maintain good posture, stay hydrated

exercises.name: Sprints
exercises.description: High-speed pedaling with moderate resistance for short bursts
exercises.modifications: Shorter sprint intervals, lower resistance
exercises.safety_notes: Proper warm-up essential, maintain control, cool down properly

exercises.name: Standing Climb
exercises.description: Pedaling while standing with high resistance to simulate uphill cycling
exercises.modifications: Lower resistance, shorter duration
exercises.safety_notes: Engage core, don't bounce, maintain controlled movement
